{:title "Tool Access Policy (Guardrails)"
 :description "Declarative predicates that enforce safety boundaries on MCP and native tool execution."
 :philosophy "Least Privilege, Fail-fast, Context-aware (Model/User)."
 :inspired-by "Talon (Policy), Hillel Wayne (Constraints)"
 :implementation-strategy
 {:core-fn "mcp-injector.policy/allow-tool?"
  :rule-types [:allow :deny]
  :matchers [:exact :regex :wildcard]}
 :acceptance-criteria
 ["Policy is an EDN map (e.g., {:allow [\"mcp__stripe__*\"] :deny [\"fs.rm\"]})."
  "Support context-aware rules: allow/deny specific tools only for specific models."
  "Integrate into `execute-tool` to block actions before side effects occur."
  "Log `tool_blocked` events to the signed Audit Trail including the policy reason."
  "Support 'dry-run' mode for safe policy testing."]
 :edge-cases
 ["Deny always wins in case of conflict."
  "LLM confusion: returning a clear 'Policy Violation' message so the agent doesn't loop forever."
  "Wildcard performance on very large tool directories."]
 :depends-on [:audit-trail]}
